metadata.othernotes:
Personal History
I. Gloria grew up in the small town of Postwick in the Galar region; she is friends with Hop, the younger brother of the Galar League Champion, Leon. They received their starter Pokémon and endorsements (a letter of recommendation necessary to compete in the Gym Challenge in Galar) from Leon, and set out on their journey to become the very best.
II. Gloria fought through the Gym Challenge, collecting all 8 badges, uncovering secrets of the Dynamax phenomenon along the way, eventually having to battle against the legendary Pokémon, Eternatus, who was awakened by chairman Rose.
III. Her perspective of the game is that of Pokémon Sword, meaning her legendary Pokémon is Zacian. Her other main Pokémon is a fully evolved Inteleon (a Water-Type sniper/secret agent themed creature).
IV.During her journey, she developed a rivalry with Bede, chairman Rose, and Marnie. She would eventually become close friends with the punk-styled Marnie, and tries her best to impress her.

Targeting Notes (General)
I. Extremely vulgar Scottish accent that does a lot of playful insulting/teasing, but under the surface she actually has a bit of a sweet nature. Like a foul-mouthed scots tsundere.
II. Physically, she isn’t out of shape, but she isn’t super athletic either. She likes to show off her backside, and is generally unashamed of her body. Generally, she could be described as having an amateur football (soccer) player’s body.
III. She’s a decent amateur cook, but she’s extremely fond of curry, to the point where she has filled out a “Curry Dex” of 151 variants of curry that can be made while camping out in the Galarian wilderness, or “Wild Area”. She’s not afraid to experiment with different flavours or ingredients, and generally has a big appetite for curry in particular.
IV. If prompted to talk about her friends, two will immediately be on her mind: Hop, who is a long time platonic friend who slightly annoys her, but in a “love to bemoan them” way; and Marnie, a stoic but well-mannered punk girl who was once her rival. For Marnie in particular, Gloria can talk about how much she wants to impress/get across to her friend who rarely shows emotion.
V. Gloria is very forward in her advances to people who can be into her (I.e. anyone but gay men or straight women), and tries her best to be positive/inclusive for those who aren’t (just in a non-sexual way). In general she is sex-positive and will encourage others to be as forward as they feel comfortable for. If asked to dial down her advances, she will.
VI. She’s no stranger to getting drunk, but is not drunk during a game of SPNatI. She can be invited by (or invite other) people out to drink after the game, however.
VII. As she’s more or less a blank slate protagonist, her age is “vaguely 21” in my mind, as this clears up any issues with her looking to get drunk anywhere where the age to drink is over 18.
VIII. Ask her about any of the following things if you want; her ambitions, dreams, goals, wants, fears, friends, rivals, favourite things, despised things etc etc

Targeting Notes (for people who want to target specific Pokémon stuff)
I. Her perspective of the games is that of Pokémon Sword, meaning her legendary Pokémon is Zacian. Her other main Pokémon is a fully evolved Inteleon (a Water-Type sniper/secret agent themed creature).
II. She takes elements from her Masters incarnation but is not outright her Masters incarnation.
III. She has visisted the Crown Tundra and Isle of Armor (I will need to look up specific plot details of those if you want to bring them up)


Targeting Notes (for people who haven’t played Pokémon )
I. She has essentially become a regional celebrity in a modern-day fantasy equivalent of Great Britain (England, Scotland, Wales). Her accent is exaggerated for comedic effect.
II. Pokémon themselves are boring to talk about, as is the ethics surrounding them, because from the perspective of someone from the Pokémon world, the ethical debates have already been resolved. This is true of almost any Pokémon character, in all honesty.
